# Cloudflare Pages headers for c0nvert
#
# IMPORTANT — Cross-Origin Isolation:
# c0nvert's video re-encode path (WebM ↔ MP4/MOV) uses ffmpeg.wasm, which
# requires SharedArrayBuffer. SharedArrayBuffer is gated behind cross-origin
# isolation, which means the document MUST set:
#   Cross-Origin-Opener-Policy: same-origin
#   Cross-Origin-Embedder-Policy: require-corp
# Without these, video re-encoding silently fails at "SharedArrayBuffer is
# not defined" and the user has to retry. MP4↔MOV stream-copy still works
# either way (pure JS, no SAB), but re-encoding does not.
#
# COEP: require-corp will BLOCK any cross-origin resource that doesn't send
# `Cross-Origin-Resource-Policy: cross-origin` or CORS headers. The CDNs we
# use (cdnjs, jsdelivr, unpkg) all send CORP, so script loads work.

/*
  Cross-Origin-Opener-Policy: same-origin
  Cross-Origin-Embedder-Policy: require-corp
  X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff
  Referrer-Policy: strict-origin-when-cross-origin
  Permissions-Policy: geolocation=(), microphone=(), camera=()
  X-Frame-Options: SAMEORIGIN

# index.html / versioned HTML — must NOT cache so deploys land immediately
/index.html
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=0, must-revalidate

/*.html
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=0, must-revalidate

# Static assets — cache for 30 days
/og.png
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=2592000, immutable

/favicon.png
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=2592000, immutable

/apple-touch-icon.png
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=2592000, immutable
